# Engineering Gates — Definition of Done

These rules are **non-negotiable** and apply to every task, including greenfield
projects where no `app/`, `spec/`, or `db/` files exist yet (so the glob-scoped
rules in `.cursor/rules/` do not auto-attach).

## When you plan

Any implementation plan (TodoWrite, Plan mode, or prose) **MUST** mirror the phases
of `.ai/workflows/new-feature.yaml` and explicitly include, as separate steps:

1. **Tests (RSpec)** — see `.ai/standards/testing.md`
2. **Review** — `ponytail-review`, `review-rails-models`, `review-db-migrations`
3. **QA sign-off** — skill `qa-plan`, no BLOCKING findings
4. **Documentation** — skill `document-module`

Never collapse these into "implementation" and never defer them to "later".

## Definition of Done

A feature, fix, or module is **NOT complete** until all of the following hold:

- [ ] **RSpec tests** cover the critical paths (happy path + auth failure +
      validation errors for endpoints; success + retryable failure for jobs).
- [ ] **No skipped/pending specs** without a ticket reference.
- [ ] **ponytail-review** passed — no unaddressed over-engineering.
- [ ] **QA** plan maps stories to tests; no BLOCKING findings.
- [ ] **Documentation** for the module/module change exists under `docs/`.
- [ ] Work happened on a `feature/<ticket>-<slug>` branch (never `main`).

## New project bootstrap

When creating a Rails app **from scratch**, the FIRST implementation step is to set
up the test stack. Follow `.ai/standards/project-bootstrap.md` (RSpec + FactoryBot +
SimpleCov + `config.generators` → `:rspec`) before writing application code.

